# ContractSentinel — Cursor Rules
# Multi-agent enterprise contract intelligence system
# github.com/kashifumair125/Contractsentinel

## What this project does
Analyzes enterprise contracts (NDA, SaaS, employment) using 5 coordinated AI agents.
Extracts clauses, checks policy violations, scores financial/legal risk, and generates
redlined rewrites. Deployed live on Railway.

## Agent architecture
Planner Agent (orchestrator) coordinates:
  Agent 1: Clause Extractor   — pdfplumber + Groq LLaMA 3.3 70B
  Agent 2: Policy Checker     — Groq LLaMA 3.3 70B  ┐ parallel via asyncio.gather()
  Agent 3: Risk Scorer        — Groq LLaMA 3.3 70B  ┘
  Agent 4: Redline Engine     — Gemini 2.0 Flash (single focused call)

## File structure
backend/main.py          — FastAPI app + all 5 agents
backend/requirements.txt — pinned dependencies
frontend/index.html      — full UI (vanilla HTML/CSS/JS, dark legal-tech theme)
Dockerfile               — PORT-aware, Railway-compatible
docker-compose.yml       — local dev

## Code rules
- All LLM calls use structured JSON output — never free-form
- Every agent prompt includes: explicit output schema + filled example + "Return ONLY valid JSON"
- Agents 2 and 3 MUST run via asyncio.gather() — never sequential
- Agent 4 (Gemini) uses google-generativeai SDK — never openai client
- All API keys from environment variables only — GROQ_API_KEY, GEMINI_API_KEY
- FastAPI endpoints are async — no sync route handlers
- Pydantic models for all agent I/O — never raw dicts

## Error handling rules
- Each agent wrapped in try/except with graceful degradation
- Pipeline does not crash if one agent fails — return partial results with error field
- Groq calls get exponential backoff retry (max 3 attempts)
- pdfplumber failures fall back to raw text extraction before raising

## Prompt engineering conventions
- System prompts are f-strings in main.py — do not split into external files
- Few-shot examples included in every structured output prompt
- Confidence threshold required for Policy Checker: "only flag if >80% confident"
- Gemini redline prompt: "Return raw text only. No markdown. No bullet points."

## What NOT to do
- Do not make agents 2 and 3 sequential — this breaks the parallel performance benchmark
- Do not hardcode PORT in Dockerfile CMD — use $PORT for Railway compatibility
- Do not use OpenAI SDK anywhere — Groq uses its own client, Gemini uses google-generativeai
- Do not add streaming to /analyze — batch response only, frontend polls /health
- Do not commit .env or any file containing GROQ_API_KEY or GEMINI_API_KEY

## Running locally
export GROQ_API_KEY="your_key"
export GEMINI_API_KEY="your_key"
cp frontend/index.html backend/static/
cd backend && uvicorn main:app --reload --port 8000

## Live deployment
Railway: contractsentinel-production-9f50.up.railway.app
/health — returns groq_configured and gemini_configured status
/analyze — POST with PDF file, returns full agent report